# Library Management System — Cursor Rules

## Architecture
- All Supabase calls go through `src/services/*Service.ts` — never in pages or feature components.
- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` only in `src/services/supabase/admin.ts` and API routes that call RPCs.
- API route order: auth → role check → Zod validation → business logic → sanitized error.

## Queries
- Never use `select('*')` — always list explicit columns.
- Book queries must include `.is('deleted_at', null)`.
- Paginate with `.range(offset, offset + pageSize - 1)` and `{ count: 'exact' }`.

## Auth
- No role picker on public registration — all signups are `member`.
- Promote staff via SQL: `UPDATE profiles SET role = 'admin' WHERE email = '...'`.

## UI
- Use shadcn/ui components from `@/components/ui`.
- Active nav link / accent: `text-brand` (see `--brand` in globals.css).
- Skeleton loaders for data tables, not spinners.
